    "content": [
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Voting and consensus mechanisms let multiple independent LLM agents evaluate the same question and combine their answers into a single decision. Because each agent votes without seeing the others' responses, the result reflects genuine independent judgment rather than one agent anchoring the rest. This is one of the simplest and most reliable ways to reduce hallucination and increase answer confidence."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "image",
        "attrs": {
          "src": "data:image/svg+xml;base64,",
          "alt": "Voting diagram: 5 independent agents vote YES/NO, aggregator counts votes and declares majority decision"
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "When to Use Voting"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "Binary or categorical answers: "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "is this code correct? Is this claim factually accurate? Which option is better? Classification tasks."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "Reducing hallucination: "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "if 4 of 5 agents give the same answer, that answer is almost certainly more reliable than any single response."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "Confidence calibration: "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "vote ratio (3/5 vs 5/5) quantifies certainty \u2014 a near-tie signals genuine ambiguity worth escalating."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "Avoid: "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "open-ended generation (\"write a summary\") where answers aren't comparable, or very long-context tasks where running N agents is prohibitively expensive."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
